      "content": "that makes sense. so basically, the \"standard\" is the western style, and then everything else is just a way to tweak it? i want to make sure my readers don't get confused. like, if someone is in Lagos or Sao Paulo, is their local way of dressing considered \"professional\" on its own, or is it more like a \"cultural version\" of the western professional look? i want to know if \"professionalism\" itself has a specific look that we're all working towards.",
